KW  - Short sale constraints
KW  - Opinion dispersion
KW  - Market efficiency
KW  - Price bubbles
KW  - Price discovery
KW  - Experimental
AB  - We test the effect of short sale constraints on market quality in an experimental setting. Short sale constrained securities trade at a premium, which is often higher than the difference between the view of the most optimistic investor and the fundamental value. Opinion dispersion contributes to overpricing; this result is more pronounced at the time opinion dispersion is induced. As time progresses, traders update their valuations with information from trading. Consequently, opinion dispersion narrows and its effect on overpricing dissipates. Under short sale constraints, the speed of price adjustment is slower, as prices never fully converge to their fundamental values.
